1. Create Database:
	- open browser and type "localhost"
	- click on "phpmyadmin" menu
	- create a database (db_abc) in MySQL
	- copy database name in a text file

2. Download WordPress:
	- go to wordpress.org
	- download latest version

3. Put WordPress(downloaded) in htdocs and rename as your project
	- copy wordpress downloaded zip file from download folder
	- go to htdocs and paste it
	- extract it
	- rename it as your project name (abc)

4. Install WordPress:
	- open browser 
	- type "localhost/abc" and press enter
	- select language: English 
	- click on "Continue" button
	- click on "Let's go" button
	- Database Setup:
		Database Name: db_abc
		Username: root
		Password: 
		Database Host: localhost
		Table Prefix: wp_

	- click on "Submit" button
	- click on "Run the installation" button
	- Website Admin Panel Setup:
		Site Title: Abc Website
		Username: admin
		Password: admin
		Confirm Password: check mark
		Your Email: admin@gmail.com
		Search Engine Visibility: un-check it (for google indexing)
	
	- click on "Install WordPress" button

5. Run Website:
	- open browser
	- type "localhost/abc" and press enter

6. Run Website Admin Panel:
	- open browser
	- type "localhost/abc/wp-admin" and press enter
	- username: admin
	- password: admin
	- click on "Log In" button

